{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1941 |Team=Oregon State Beavers |Image= |ImageSize=200px |Conference=Pacific Coast Conference |ShortConference=PCC |CoachRank= |APRank=12 |Record=8-2 |ConfRecord=7-2 |HeadCoach=[[Lon Stiner]] |StadiumArena=[[Bell Field]] |Champion= Rose Bowl Champions |BowlTourney= [[1942 Rose Bowl|Rose Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult= W 20-16 vs. [[Duke Blue Devils football|Duke]] }} {{1941 PCC football standings}} The '''1941 [[Oregon State Beavers football]] team''' represented [[Oregon State University|Oregon State College]] in the [[1941 college football season]]. The Beavers ended this season with eight wins and two losses. They were the [[Pacific Coast Conference]] champions and won the [[1942 Rose Bowl]] over [[Duke Blue Devils football|Duke]]. Because of the Japanese [[attack on Pearl Harbor]], the Rose Bowl was held in [[Durham, North Carolina]]. Oregon State thus became the only team to win a Rose Bowl outside of [[Pasadena, California]]. The Beavers scored 143 points and allowed 49 points. The team was led by head coach [[Lon Stiner]].
==Schedule==
The Beavers finished the season with an 8&ndash;2 record, 7&ndash;2 in the [[Pacific Coast Conference]]. Ranks are based on the time the game was played.
